  "prompt": "Is it too late for any age person to learn computer programing?",
  "response": "No, it is never too late for anyone to learn computer programming, regardless of their age. People of all ages can learn new skills, including programming, as long as they have the motivation and access to the necessary resources. There are numerous online courses, tutorials, coding bootcamps, and community groups that can help learners at any stage of life. Additionally, learning programming can provide cognitive benefits, enhance problem-solving skills, and potentially open up new career opportunities. Age should not be a barrier to acquiring new knowledge and skills.",
